ct, this is the first book to include a proof of this famous result since its original publication. Theorem 4.1.2 is followed by a systematic study of the structure of spherical buildings and their automorphism groups based on the Moufang property. Moufang buildings of rank two were recently classified by Tits and Weiss. The last chapter provides an overview of the classification of spherical buildings, one that reflects these and other important developments.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aBuildings (Group theory). 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economics / Macroeconomics.2bisacsh  aBN-pair.  aTits system.  aWeyl distance.  aWeyl group.  aadjacent.  abipartite.  abuilding.  acomplex.  aconcatenation.  adeletion.  aedge coloring.  aendomorphism.  afolding.  afree group.  agallery.  agirth.  agraph.  ainsertion.  ainvolution.  aisometry.  amultiple edge.  aoctonion division algebra.  apanel.  apath.  apre-gallery.  arealizable.  aregular group action.  aroot group.  askew-hermitian form.  asub-chamber system.  asubbuilding.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044250240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691216041zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691216041423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691216041.jpg  a978-3-11-044250-2  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK